{
  "name": "8761-mcp-secret-redaction",
  "target_process": "warp-oss",
  "_purpose": "Comprehensive truth-table evidence for warpdotdev/warp#10839 (fixes #8761), running against a warp-oss binary that has three locally-applied patches matching warpdotdev/warp#11262 (SECRETS_REGEX compile on safe_mode toggle), #11263 (raw-input redaction scan before env/headers templatization), and #11265 (redaction predicate on the new-server '+ Add' save path). The recipe is **state-agnostic at boot**: a normalize step (click_at_if_text 'Secret visual redaction mode') drives the toggle to OFF regardless of whether cloud sync arrived with SafeModeEnabled=true or false. Then six phases: (A) confirm OFF, (B) toggle ON and prove the dropdown appears, (C) prove the redaction is working (sk- save BLOCKED), (D) toggle OFF, (E) prove the OFF-half of the truth table (same sk- save SUCCEEDS and the API key is preserved verbatim), (F) toggle back ON and prove the redaction state is returned (dropdown re-appears).",
  "_safety": "Token is the deterministic placeholder `sk-FAKE0000000000FAKEdemoWARP10839v2` \u2014 clearly not a real credential. Matches the Generic SK regex `\\bsk-[a-zA-Z0-9\\-]{10,100}\\b` from the persisted custom_secret_regex_list.",
  "_state_touched": "Phase E adds MCP entry `demo-pr10839-v2` to warp-oss's MY MCPS list. Toggles `Settings \u2192 Privacy \u2192 Secret redaction` OFF \u2192 ON \u2192 OFF \u2192 ON during the recording (ends ON, matching the safer default for the user's environment). Pre-condition: warp-oss launched with an empty mcp_server_installations table and the toggle in its observed default OFF state. User pre-approved leaving demo-pr10839-v2 in place after the recording.",
  "_phases": [
    "A: open Settings, search 'redaction'; visually confirm toggle is OFF (no 'Secret visual redaction mode' dropdown)",
    "B: click toggle ON (fires #11262 patch \u2192 SECRETS_REGEX recompile); wait for 'Secret visual redaction mode' dropdown",
    "C: prove redaction works \u2014 navigate to MCP Servers \u2192 + Add \u2192 paste config with sk- in headers.Authorization \u2192 Save \u2192 expect 'contains secrets' toast and no entry in MY MCPS",
    "D: dismiss dialog, navigate back to Secret redaction, click toggle OFF",
    "E: prove OFF allows save \u2014 navigate to MCP Servers \u2192 + Add \u2192 paste same config \u2192 Save \u2192 expect demo-pr10839-v2 to appear in MY MCPS with the sk- API key preserved verbatim",
    "F: prove the toggle returns \u2014 navigate back to Secret redaction, click toggle ON, wait for 'Secret visual redaction mode' dropdown to re-appear"
  ],
